WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:03.960
Dre: The Johnson family
loves Halloween.

00:03.960 --> 00:05.670
We love the decorating...

00:05.670 --> 00:07.580
the trick-or-treating.

00:07.580 --> 00:09.460
We love the mischief.

00:09.460 --> 00:11.920
But what we love most
is showing out

00:11.920 --> 00:13.920
in our family costume.

00:13.920 --> 00:18.210
Now, choosing the perfect
costume isn't always easy.

00:18.210 --> 00:21.420
Sometimes we're
cartoon superheroes.

00:21.420 --> 00:24.620
Sometimes we're real heroes.

00:24.620 --> 00:27.500
But this year,
we get to be both.

00:27.500 --> 00:31.040
Because of "Black Panther,"
we not only own the box office,

00:31.040 --> 00:32.710
we own Halloween.

00:32.710 --> 00:34.170
All: Wakanda forever!

00:34.170 --> 00:35.170
Mm!

00:35.170 --> 00:36.790
All right. Halloween
dress rehearsal.

00:36.790 --> 00:39.420
You two need
to put on these.

00:39.420 --> 00:41.250
Yeah.

00:41.250 --> 00:43.620
We're not dressing up
this year.

00:43.620 --> 00:45.880
But we got Black Panther.

00:45.880 --> 00:48.960
And it took me two hours
to do all of this.

00:48.960 --> 00:51.670
And it took me two days
to do all this.

00:56.620 --> 01:01.710
♪♪

01:01.710 --> 01:05.000
But why are you guys
not dressing up?

01:05.000 --> 01:06.710
No one is.
What?

01:06.710 --> 01:09.000
No one in our school's
even doing Halloween.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.120
The only thing going on
is Cameron Carter's party,

01:11.120 --> 01:13.620
and fingers crossed
we get invited.

01:13.620 --> 01:15.290
Well, of course you guys
are gonna get invited.

01:15.290 --> 01:17.750
Are you kidding me?
You're adorbs.

01:17.750 --> 01:19.380
It's very exclusive.

01:19.380 --> 01:22.380
I mean, he only has been giving
out two invitations a day,

01:22.380 --> 01:24.000
and tomorrow's the last two.

01:24.000 --> 01:25.670
That is so cruel.

01:25.670 --> 01:28.750
Nuh-unh.
That is so cool.

01:28.750 --> 01:30.080
Build the hype.

01:30.080 --> 01:32.580
Then people suck up to you
to be a part of that hype.

01:32.580 --> 01:35.830
Then you create the demand
for the hype.

01:35.830 --> 01:37.500
Oh, I got to meet
this dude Cameron.

01:37.500 --> 01:39.000
It's Cameron Carter.

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
He's so cool,
he has full-name status.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.420
I do not think Cameron Carter
is so cool.

01:44.420 --> 01:45.710
Who does he think he is?

01:45.710 --> 01:48.120
Look, we don't have time to
explain Cameron Carter to you.

01:48.120 --> 01:50.670
Oh. Well, she told you.
Someone's very busy.
My goodness.

01:50.670 --> 01:53.920
[ Chuckles ]
And so it begins.

01:53.920 --> 01:55.170
What are you talking about?

01:55.170 --> 01:57.330
Seventh grade.

01:57.330 --> 01:59.040
It's like a blood bath.

01:59.040 --> 02:01.080
You make one mistake,
and you're dead.

02:01.080 --> 02:03.420
Like my seventh grade hike
to the Falls.

02:03.420 --> 02:04.710
The Falls.

02:04.710 --> 02:07.170
I forgot to put a protein bar
in my backpack,

02:07.170 --> 02:09.420
and I fainted
from exhaustion.

02:09.420 --> 02:13.170
When I awoke, I was being
carried by a small girl

02:13.170 --> 02:16.460
like we were on our honeymoon
in the Poconos.

02:16.460 --> 02:17.620
[ Exhales deeply ]

02:17.620 --> 02:19.250
Ladies' man rep
gone like that.

02:19.250 --> 02:20.620
You had a ladies' man rep?

02:20.620 --> 02:22.830
You don't sweep
the math awards

02:22.830 --> 02:25.120
and not become
a ladies' man.

02:27.540 --> 02:28.540
Bow...
Yeah.

02:28.540 --> 02:29.790
Don't listen to him.

02:29.790 --> 02:31.330
Your son's a weirdo.

02:31.330 --> 02:33.330
The twins,
they'll be all right.

02:33.330 --> 02:35.420
No, he's right.

02:35.420 --> 02:38.040
I remember in seventh grade,

02:38.040 --> 02:42.330
I washed my hair
and I let it air dry.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.750
And my mom, she said
I looked like

02:44.750 --> 02:49.000
a beautiful
African princess.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.830
It didn't dry the way
I thought it would.

02:51.830 --> 02:54.000
Sorry, no room...

02:54.000 --> 02:56.540
Helmet Hair.

02:56.540 --> 02:58.170
Helmet Hair?

02:58.170 --> 02:59.330
That's hilarious!

02:59.330 --> 03:00.790
No, it's not!

03:00.790 --> 03:04.170
Dre, they voted me "Most Likely
to Survive a Car Crash."

03:04.170 --> 03:06.670
Also hilarious.
Oh, my God.
You know what...

03:06.670 --> 03:08.120
Where the hell did you go
to middle school, Bow?

03:08.120 --> 03:09.040
The Apollo?

03:09.040 --> 03:10.420
This is serious, Dre.

03:10.420 --> 03:11.960
Seventh grade is hard enough

03:11.960 --> 03:14.620
without being excluded
from parties.

03:16.170 --> 03:17.790
We need to go talk
to the school.

03:17.790 --> 03:19.250
It's just one party

03:19.250 --> 03:21.670
that they still
might get invited to.

03:21.670 --> 03:24.460
And if they don't,
then they'll deal with it.

03:24.460 --> 03:26.580
And how did you deal
with being left out

03:26.580 --> 03:27.790
in seventh grade?

03:27.790 --> 03:31.500
I was the king
of seventh grade.

03:31.500 --> 03:32.960
I never took a loss.

03:32.960 --> 03:34.540
♪♪

03:34.540 --> 03:38.000
Junior, thanks for helping me
pick up the dry cleaning.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.830
Those choir robes are heavy.

03:39.830 --> 03:41.830
Yeah, thank you for
helping me fill my day.

03:41.830 --> 03:45.120
Gap year is definitely off
to a slow start.

03:45.120 --> 03:47.290
You ever feel like you've read
the whole Internet?

03:47.290 --> 03:49.670
You ever feel like
you didn't wash your...

03:49.670 --> 03:52.000
face this morning?
I --

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
Hey, Miss Ruby.

03:54.000 --> 03:55.080
So good to see you.

03:55.080 --> 03:57.330
Oh, honey, it's good
to see you, too.

03:57.330 --> 03:58.670
[ Chuckles ]

03:58.670 --> 04:01.330
We are so gonna need
your voice tonight.

04:01.330 --> 04:04.000
Oh, well, you know me.
When the Lord calls...

04:04.000 --> 04:08.290
♪ I come running! ♪

04:08.290 --> 04:09.290
Who's this?

04:09.290 --> 04:12.080
Niecy, this is my grandson,
Junior.

04:12.080 --> 04:12.830
Nice to meet you.

04:12.830 --> 04:14.500
Niecy's our little star.

04:14.500 --> 04:17.170
She's been with us since
she was 10 years old.

04:17.170 --> 04:19.540
I poached her
from First Faith.

04:19.540 --> 04:21.500
Place fell on the skids
after that.

04:21.500 --> 04:24.330
It's an Olive's Garden now.
[ Laughs ]

04:24.330 --> 04:27.080
Go, Niecy.
Give him a little taste.

04:27.080 --> 04:29.920
♪ Oh, Happy Day ♪

04:29.920 --> 04:33.380
♪ When Jesus washed ♪

04:33.380 --> 04:36.170
♪ He washed my sins away ♪

04:36.170 --> 04:37.120
Wow.

04:37.120 --> 04:40.000
She's never going secular.
[ Chuckles ]

04:40.000 --> 04:43.250
All right, you two
little babies chat, okay?

04:43.250 --> 04:45.880
But, uh,
don't let him bore you

04:45.880 --> 04:48.960
talking about that wizard
Harvey Porter

04:48.960 --> 04:51.670
who fights
those hog wars.

04:51.670 --> 04:52.920
[ Mutters ]

04:52.920 --> 04:55.170
It's Harry Potter, Grandma.
Yeah, yeah.

04:55.170 --> 04:57.880
I haven't read those books
in years, so...

04:57.880 --> 04:59.790
Yeah, me neither.

04:59.790 --> 05:01.330
I actually just
re-read them.

05:01.330 --> 05:02.460
Me, too.

05:02.460 --> 05:03.960
They hold up, right?

05:03.960 --> 05:06.330
A story for all ages.

05:07.670 --> 05:10.620
Anyway, what's your story?

05:10.620 --> 05:13.750
You, uh, go to college
on the first try?

05:13.750 --> 05:15.710
[ Laughs ]

05:17.330 --> 05:19.670
[ Sighs loudly ]

05:19.670 --> 05:21.710
Hello.
Hi.

05:21.710 --> 05:24.540
Hello, Principal Biggs.

05:24.540 --> 05:27.210
I can't get your kids invited
to Cameron Carter's party.

05:27.210 --> 05:28.620
Dang it.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.000
I told her.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.210
Doesn't this school
have a rule

05:32.210 --> 05:34.380
about everybody getting
invited to everything?

05:34.380 --> 05:35.830
For elementary kids.

05:35.830 --> 05:39.040
But this is middle school,
so it's kill or be killed.

05:39.040 --> 05:40.080
Mm-hmm.
What?
That sounds very violent.

05:40.080 --> 05:41.830
Don't worry, the kids
figure it out.

05:41.830 --> 05:43.920
Told her that, too.

05:43.920 --> 05:45.250
Is there anything
you can do?

05:45.250 --> 05:48.540
Listen, if I could fix
middle school for anyone,

05:48.540 --> 05:50.830
I'd go back and fix it
for myself.
Okay.

05:50.830 --> 05:52.710
The summer between sixth
and seventh grade,

05:52.710 --> 05:54.710
I grew 2 1/2 feet.

05:54.710 --> 05:55.670
Did you join the league?

05:55.670 --> 05:56.540
They thought I was
a teacher.

05:56.540 --> 05:57.540
What?
Or a Yeti.

05:57.540 --> 05:58.670
That's why I became
a teacher.

05:58.670 --> 06:00.210
Mm-hmm.
Right. Okay.

06:00.210 --> 06:03.170
Anyway, my advice is just
to stay out of it.

06:03.170 --> 06:06.000
I told her that, too,

06:06.000 --> 06:07.420
but she don't listen.
Dre.

06:07.420 --> 06:09.170
Now, look, Principal Biggs,
we'll get out of your way.

06:09.170 --> 06:10.790
You go on and do your job.

06:10.790 --> 06:13.040
Thank you.
Thank you.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.250
You heard her, Bow.

06:14.250 --> 06:16.380
[ Scoffs ] What do teachers
know about children?

06:16.380 --> 06:17.830
We need to do
something, Dre.

06:17.830 --> 06:20.000
Why?

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
Look at them.
Look at Jack.

06:22.000 --> 06:24.500
He's all cocky, kicking it
on top of the table.

06:24.500 --> 06:26.420
He's --
And --
And look at Diane,

06:26.420 --> 06:28.040
ruling the roost.

06:28.040 --> 06:29.960
She looks pretty.
Uh-huh.

06:29.960 --> 06:32.210
They are fine, Bow.
Come on. Let's go.
Okay.

06:32.210 --> 06:33.920
Cameron: Yo!
Final invitations!

06:33.920 --> 06:35.290
Saved the best for last.

06:35.290 --> 06:37.000
Get over here, you two.

06:37.000 --> 06:38.750
Oh, my God! Yes!

06:38.750 --> 06:40.620
Okay. Okay.
See? Winners.

06:40.620 --> 06:42.040
Okay.

06:42.040 --> 06:44.540
Thank you.
Whoa, what are you doing?

06:44.540 --> 06:47.040
These are for them.

06:47.040 --> 06:49.380
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:49.380 --> 06:52.170
We were -- We were just
excitedly walking this way.

06:52.170 --> 06:54.120
Yeah, let's just --
just go.
Let's go, yeah.

06:54.120 --> 06:56.080
Wait, you thought
those were for you?

06:56.080 --> 06:58.080
You guys are so thirsty.

06:58.080 --> 06:59.750
Hey, everybody!
Hold on to your drinks.

06:59.750 --> 07:01.830
It's the Thirsty Twins!

07:01.830 --> 07:04.880
[ Chanting ]
Thir-sty Twins! Thir-sty Twins!

07:04.880 --> 07:07.750
Thir-sty Twins! Thir-sty Twins!

07:07.750 --> 07:09.540
Thir-sty Twins! Thir-sty Twins!

07:09.540 --> 07:10.670
Oh, God.

07:11.920 --> 07:14.040
Hey, baby! Don't forget
your new book bag!

07:14.040 --> 07:15.250
Ah. Thanks, Mom!

07:15.250 --> 07:16.500
All right.

07:18.500 --> 07:19.880
Boy: Kid's got a purse!

07:19.880 --> 07:21.500
[ Laughter ]

07:23.580 --> 07:25.330
I did take a loss.

07:25.330 --> 07:27.210
Thir-sty Twins! Thir-sty Twins!

07:27.210 --> 07:30.000
Thir-sty Twins! Thir-sty Twins!

07:30.000 --> 07:31.620
Okay, we've got
to do something.

07:31.620 --> 07:33.580
Yeah, I'm about to punch a kid.
Hold my purse.

07:33.580 --> 07:34.540
[ Screaming ] No!
What?

07:38.710 --> 07:39.920
I can't believe
they clowned my kids!

07:39.920 --> 07:41.750
Yeah, i-if it was Junior,
yeah, I'd understand,

07:41.750 --> 07:43.500
but this was Jack and Diane.

07:43.500 --> 07:46.170
Diane's petty
and she's mean

07:46.170 --> 07:49.250
and she messed up my meet
and greet with Boyz II Men,

07:49.250 --> 07:51.620
but she's no loser.

07:51.620 --> 07:53.170
I wish there was a way
that I could put

07:53.170 --> 07:55.170
this Cameron Carter
in his place.

07:55.170 --> 07:57.580
Oh-ho-ho! Let's go
on the Dark Web

07:57.580 --> 08:00.250
and find a child assassin.

08:00.250 --> 08:02.960
Now, do you want a child
who's an assassin

08:02.960 --> 08:05.580
or a grown man
who kills children?

08:05.580 --> 08:06.830
What?

08:06.830 --> 08:07.920
Neither!

08:07.920 --> 08:10.330
Fine, that's the last time
I try to help.

08:10.330 --> 08:12.080
So, you need
a sensible plan.

08:12.080 --> 08:14.170
You need to get a disguise,
go undercover,

08:14.170 --> 08:17.000
and enroll in the school
as a cooler kid

08:17.000 --> 08:19.170
named Cameron Carter.
-Hmm.

08:19.170 --> 08:21.880
That's also
a terrible plan.

08:21.880 --> 08:23.580
It's like he just
comes here to talk,

08:23.580 --> 08:24.620
but he doesn't
need our help, right?

08:24.620 --> 08:25.620
You feel that
in your spirit?

08:25.620 --> 08:27.210
Some people
just want you to listen.

08:27.210 --> 08:28.880
Dre, if you don't
have the stones

08:28.880 --> 08:31.330
to hire a black-market
Internet assassin,

08:31.330 --> 08:35.250
what you need to do is throw
a kick-ass rival party.

08:35.250 --> 08:37.580
Oh, like Reese Witherspoon
in "Big Little Lies."

08:37.580 --> 08:40.210
[ Scoffs ] Amabella's party
didn't stand a chance.

08:40.210 --> 08:44.380
You know, a rival party
just might work.

08:44.380 --> 08:45.580
Wonderful,

08:45.580 --> 08:48.040
because Interpol just seized
Josh's computer.

08:48.040 --> 08:49.120
There you go.
What are you doing?

08:49.120 --> 08:50.710
Fingerprints on that.
I got to go.

08:50.710 --> 08:52.170
No, no, no, no.
No, no, no!

08:52.170 --> 08:53.330
This isn't --
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

08:53.330 --> 08:54.580
Oh, it just took
my picture.

08:54.580 --> 08:57.500
Yes, I understand that is
the school policy,

08:57.500 --> 09:00.250
Dean Reynolds,
but what about the mom policy,

09:00.250 --> 09:03.000
which states
that you expel any kid

09:03.000 --> 09:05.790
that is mean to my kid?

09:05.790 --> 09:08.670
Uh, no, I think
you're being unreasonable.

09:08.670 --> 09:10.710
Uh, okay, yeah, thank you.

09:10.710 --> 09:13.040
I am getting nowhere
with the school board.

09:13.040 --> 09:14.540
Don't worry about it,
all right?

09:14.540 --> 09:15.880
I got a better plan.

09:15.880 --> 09:18.330
Forget Cameron Carter.

09:18.330 --> 09:20.290
We are throwing
our own party.

09:20.290 --> 09:21.750
Kids! Get down here!

09:21.750 --> 09:23.250
A rival party?
Mm-hmm.

09:23.250 --> 09:26.290
[ Gasps ] That is way faster
than suing the school.

09:26.290 --> 09:27.290
What?
I love that.

09:27.290 --> 09:28.460
Uh, okay.
I love it!

09:28.460 --> 09:29.460
Okay, come on.
Come in here. Sit down.

09:29.460 --> 09:30.880
Come on. Sit down.
Sit down.

09:30.880 --> 09:32.330
Come on. Hurry up.
Sit down. Cop a squat.
Yes. Come on.

09:32.330 --> 09:33.830
Okay, sitting down.
All right.

09:33.830 --> 09:37.420
We are going to save
your social life.

09:37.420 --> 09:38.460
Ha!
Mm-hmm.

09:38.460 --> 09:39.500
It's too late.
Hmm.

09:39.500 --> 09:41.290
The janitor in
the lower school told me

09:41.290 --> 09:42.330
to keep my chin up...
Mnh-mnh.

09:42.330 --> 09:43.790
...but also
wouldn't give me dap.

09:43.790 --> 09:46.120
Have no fear, little lady.

09:46.120 --> 09:48.500
Your father and I
are gonna throw a party

09:48.500 --> 09:51.380
that is way better
than Cameron Whatever's.

09:51.380 --> 09:52.210
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]

09:52.210 --> 09:53.330
You know it's Carter.

09:53.330 --> 09:55.960
I am taking away
his power.

09:55.960 --> 09:56.920
Snatch it.

09:56.920 --> 09:58.250
Yeah, but won't
everyone think

09:58.250 --> 10:00.540
the Thirsty Twins
are just throwing a party

10:00.540 --> 10:02.500
because we didn't get invited
to Cameron Carter's?

10:02.500 --> 10:04.210
No!

10:04.210 --> 10:07.210
Because your party will be
bigger, blacker, and deffer,

10:07.210 --> 10:08.500
like a Chris Rock special.

10:08.500 --> 10:09.960
Yeah, way better.

10:09.960 --> 10:10.830
Mm-hmm.

10:10.830 --> 10:12.000
How?

10:12.000 --> 10:13.500
Well, um...
Okay, uh, yeah.
Good question.

10:13.500 --> 10:14.500
Yeah.
How?

10:14.500 --> 10:15.580
We're, um...

10:15.580 --> 10:17.960
Uh, because i-it's
gonna be a --

10:17.960 --> 10:19.460
be a-a-a...

10:19.460 --> 10:22.000
haunted house party.
Haunted house party!

10:22.000 --> 10:23.750
Yes!
[ Laughs evilly ]

10:23.750 --> 10:27.080
Yes! That leads
to a pizza party

10:27.080 --> 10:29.710
with a deejay
in the backyard.

10:29.710 --> 10:30.880
Yes!
Yes! Oh!

10:30.880 --> 10:34.040
And then we are gonna
sue the school!

10:34.040 --> 10:35.670
[ Grunts ]
Let's back it up
just a little bit.

10:35.670 --> 10:36.830
Okay, it's --

10:36.830 --> 10:39.960
I am going to use
all of my resources at work.

10:39.960 --> 10:40.920
Okay.
Okay, I'm --

10:40.920 --> 10:42.380
I'm gonna get
a special-effects guy...

10:42.380 --> 10:46.120
Pssh!
...gonna hire a hair
and makeup professional.

10:46.120 --> 10:50.880
And I will get real blood
from the hospital.

10:50.880 --> 10:52.250
What?
She might.

10:52.250 --> 10:53.120
Yeah.

10:53.120 --> 10:54.750
Your reps are
in the gutter,

10:54.750 --> 10:56.420
and ain't no way
we gonna half-step.

10:56.420 --> 10:57.460
Mnh-mnh.
All right?

10:57.460 --> 11:00.000
So get on board.
Mm-hmm.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.580
I don't know.

11:02.580 --> 11:03.670
We're still not sold, dawg.

11:03.670 --> 11:04.750
Aw, man.
Yeah.

11:04.750 --> 11:06.380
Look, shouldn't we just
accept our place

11:06.380 --> 11:08.540
and keep our heads down
until this all blows over?

11:08.540 --> 11:10.290
It won't.

11:10.290 --> 11:11.960
Kids never forget.

11:11.960 --> 11:13.710
Ever.

11:13.710 --> 11:15.170
32 years ago...

11:15.170 --> 11:16.540
Oh, boy. Here we go.

11:16.540 --> 11:18.460
...your grandma made me
carry a book bag

11:18.460 --> 11:20.710
that looked like a purse.

11:20.710 --> 11:23.830
Let's see how my friends
let that go.

11:23.830 --> 11:25.040
Yeah.

11:25.040 --> 11:26.790
"7th grade memories?"

11:26.790 --> 11:28.330
Bam. Look at that.

11:28.330 --> 11:31.750
-Your purse, Purse Boy!
-Dre's punk-ass purse.

11:31.750 --> 11:34.710
Ronnie: My mom died.
Also, your purse!

11:34.710 --> 11:36.330
32 years later,

11:36.330 --> 11:38.960
and I'm still Purse Boy.

11:38.960 --> 11:40.670
Yeah.

11:40.670 --> 11:42.290
Okay, we're in.

11:42.290 --> 11:44.880
Aw, yes! Okay.

11:44.880 --> 11:47.580
This party is gonna be lit!

11:47.580 --> 11:48.750
I regret it already.
Sh-Sh-She's not

11:48.750 --> 11:50.080
gonna say that
when your friends are here.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.460
I make no promises.

11:51.460 --> 11:53.000
[ Groans ]

11:53.000 --> 11:55.830
♪♪

11:55.830 --> 11:57.460
[ Door closes ]

11:57.460 --> 11:59.750
Hey. You just getting home?

11:59.750 --> 12:01.830
Yeah, I was just hanging out
with a friend.

12:01.830 --> 12:02.960
All night?

12:02.960 --> 12:04.670
Yeah, I'm pretty tired.

12:04.670 --> 12:06.670
You want Grandma to make you
a cup of tea, baby?

12:06.670 --> 12:08.330
No, I just need
to rehydrate.

12:08.330 --> 12:09.500
Okay.

12:09.500 --> 12:10.460
[ Sighs ]

12:10.460 --> 12:12.830
♪ Oh, Happy Day ♪

12:12.830 --> 12:14.540
Whoo. Electrolytes...

12:15.920 --> 12:17.170
Mmm.

12:17.170 --> 12:19.620
♪ Oh, Happy Day ♪

12:19.620 --> 12:21.000
Okay, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey.

12:21.000 --> 12:22.210
Come here.

12:22.210 --> 12:25.170
What friend were you
hanging out with last night?

12:25.170 --> 12:26.830
I was with Niecy.

12:26.830 --> 12:28.380
Okay.

12:28.380 --> 12:31.920
So, were you with her...

12:31.920 --> 12:36.250
or were you with her?

12:36.250 --> 12:38.500
Um, I think
the second one?

12:38.500 --> 12:41.830
Aw, Junior,
I don't believe you.

12:41.830 --> 12:43.710
You can't be running around
my church,

12:43.710 --> 12:45.790
having relations
with people.

12:45.790 --> 12:47.620
Yeah, it -- it was definitely
the second one.

12:47.620 --> 12:50.750
Do you know how clucky
those church hens are?

12:50.750 --> 12:52.620
They're gonna be gossiping
all over the place

12:52.620 --> 12:55.500
about me
and my gigolo grandson

12:55.500 --> 12:58.000
taking advantage of
that sweet little girl.

12:58.000 --> 13:00.670
Niecy texted me,
"You up?" and...

13:00.670 --> 13:02.920
Not one more word
out of you, young man.

13:02.920 --> 13:04.170
Go to your room.

13:04.170 --> 13:06.120
Go to your room and
think about what you did.

13:06.120 --> 13:07.000
Really?

13:07.000 --> 13:08.620
No. No.
Go to your room

13:08.620 --> 13:10.540
and don't think about
what you did.

13:10.540 --> 13:12.750
Get out of here!

13:12.750 --> 13:14.670
The hell is wrong
with you?

13:15.920 --> 13:17.500
Jack: Oh, man.

13:17.500 --> 13:19.580
I didn't think you guys
could do this.

13:19.580 --> 13:21.670
I mean, you got the whole
seventh grade here,

13:21.670 --> 13:23.170
even Cameron Carter.

13:23.170 --> 13:24.920
Diane: Whoa,
and Emily Copeland.

13:24.920 --> 13:27.040
I heard her mom lets her
have co-ed sleepovers.

13:27.040 --> 13:30.750
What?
I told you we would
deliver the cool kids.

13:30.750 --> 13:35.120
Now, go,
and own this moment.

13:35.120 --> 13:37.880
Jack Johnson, Diane Johnson.

13:37.880 --> 13:39.420
You take
your full-name status

13:39.420 --> 13:41.670
and you just rub it
in everybody's faces.

13:41.670 --> 13:43.580
Go. Go on.

13:43.580 --> 13:47.500
Welcome to a Jack Johnson
and Diane Johnson production

13:47.500 --> 13:50.250
of the scariest night
of your life!

13:50.250 --> 13:51.290
-Yes!
-Whoo!

13:51.290 --> 13:52.750
Oh, and do not forget
to stick around

13:52.750 --> 13:55.330
for the after party,
where there's gonna be a deejay

13:55.330 --> 13:57.670
who will play radio edits
of all your favorite songs.

13:57.670 --> 13:58.960
This is lit!

13:58.960 --> 14:01.540
Yeah! That's exactly what
I said, Cameron Carter.

14:01.540 --> 14:02.330
This is lit!

14:02.330 --> 14:04.380
Like, I am legit scared.

14:04.380 --> 14:05.670
This place is hype!

14:05.670 --> 14:07.040
Hyp--

14:07.040 --> 14:08.330
The Hype Twins!

14:08.330 --> 14:10.170
-Oh!
-The Hype Twins!

14:10.170 --> 14:12.170
[ Chanting ]
Hype Twins! Hype Twins!

14:12.170 --> 14:13.880
Hype Twins! Hype Twins!

14:13.880 --> 14:15.620
Hype Twins! Hype Twins!

14:15.620 --> 14:16.620
Hype Twins!

14:16.620 --> 14:17.880
We did it.

14:17.880 --> 14:19.290
We saved our kids.
Yes.

14:19.290 --> 14:20.830
Oh, my God. Look.
Go on in.

14:20.830 --> 14:22.210
Oh, look at that!

14:23.170 --> 14:25.210
Are you okay?
[ Voice breaking ] Yeah.

14:25.210 --> 14:28.460
I, uh, just never thought that
I'd be such a good father.

14:28.460 --> 14:29.290
Oh.

14:30.540 --> 14:33.620
[ Children screaming ]

14:33.620 --> 14:36.500
It's a haunted house!
It's supposed to be scary!

14:36.500 --> 14:38.750
Don't leave! There's pizza!

14:38.750 --> 14:41.920
No! The pizza's a trap!
It's all a trap!

14:41.920 --> 14:44.330
It wasn't real.
It wasn't real.

14:44.330 --> 14:45.830
That baby had a knife!

14:45.830 --> 14:47.290
Where's Joshua?

14:47.290 --> 14:49.330
Has anyone seen Joshua?

14:50.330 --> 14:51.710
Uh...

14:51.710 --> 14:54.040
I think if we find Joshua...

14:55.040 --> 14:56.790
...we can turn this around.

14:56.790 --> 14:58.250
[ Demonic laughter ]

15:02.120 --> 15:03.710
Hey, guys.
Hey.

15:03.710 --> 15:05.080
Pizza delivery.

15:05.080 --> 15:07.880
If you like, there's
40 more boxes downstairs.

15:07.880 --> 15:09.250
Yep, 40 more.

15:09.250 --> 15:10.670
Just go.

15:10.670 --> 15:12.120
I'm too upset to eat.

15:12.120 --> 15:13.710
We're sorry, all right?

15:13.710 --> 15:16.620
We were -- We were just
trying to help.
Yeah.

15:16.620 --> 15:18.830
And in a way,
we did help, you know?
Yeah.

15:18.830 --> 15:21.670
Because now, no one's gonna
talk about how lame you were

15:21.670 --> 15:23.000
at school the other day.

15:25.540 --> 15:26.960
Aw, buddy.
Aw, I need a hug, too.

15:26.960 --> 15:28.290
Pepperoni or cheese?

15:28.290 --> 15:29.420
Oh.

15:32.210 --> 15:34.290
How did we
mess this up so bad?

15:34.290 --> 15:36.290
Well, we were just trying
to save our kids

15:36.290 --> 15:38.170
from being Helmet Hair
and Purse Boy.

15:38.170 --> 15:39.330
I know.

15:39.330 --> 15:40.880
Talking about that
seventh-grade purse?

15:40.880 --> 15:43.420
Yeah, it ruined
middle school for me.

15:43.420 --> 15:47.170
Your Jheri curl and
all those Chocodiles you ate

15:47.170 --> 15:49.040
ruined middle school
for you.

15:49.040 --> 15:50.580
But you got through it,
didn't you?

15:50.580 --> 15:53.290
If we can make things
a little less awful

15:53.290 --> 15:55.000
for our kids,
shouldn't we?

15:55.000 --> 15:56.120
No.

15:56.120 --> 15:59.000
Middle school is terrible
no matter what.

15:59.000 --> 16:01.580
Now, I know you want
to protect the kids

16:01.580 --> 16:03.920
from the pain of growing up,
but you can't.

16:03.920 --> 16:07.830
What you can do is teach them
they can handle it.

16:07.830 --> 16:09.830
She's not wrong.
Mm-hmm.

16:09.830 --> 16:11.670
It's about resilience.
Mm-hmm.

16:11.670 --> 16:15.880
I didn't let being called
Helmet Hair break me.

16:15.880 --> 16:19.000
Pushing through
made me stronger.

16:19.000 --> 16:22.330
And that's why you have the
strength to go out in the world

16:22.330 --> 16:25.580
looking like a hot mess
the way you do every day.

16:28.040 --> 16:32.040
I am a beautiful
African princess.

16:32.040 --> 16:33.830
Look, Ma,

16:33.830 --> 16:36.120
it's not easy
watching your kids grow up.

16:36.120 --> 16:38.420
Yeah. It happens fast.

16:38.420 --> 16:40.330
One day they're getting
called names

16:40.330 --> 16:43.290
and the next day,
they're sleeping with

16:43.290 --> 16:46.960
the principal soloist
in your church choir.

16:46.960 --> 16:48.330
Mama, what you
talking about?

16:48.330 --> 16:51.290
Oh, it's just something
I saw on "Scandal."

16:51.290 --> 16:52.500
The what?

16:52.500 --> 16:53.750
Eh...

16:55.000 --> 16:56.330
Excuse me.
Aah!

16:56.330 --> 16:58.420
I'm Joshua Miller.

16:58.420 --> 17:00.960
I'm looking for my parents.

17:00.960 --> 17:02.960
Um, you --
Okay.

17:02.960 --> 17:05.210
Uh, come this way, dear.

17:05.210 --> 17:09.040
♪♪

17:09.040 --> 17:11.380
Junior, there you are.

17:11.380 --> 17:13.580
Grandma, before
you throw that at me,

17:13.580 --> 17:15.040
you've got
your church back.

17:15.040 --> 17:16.790
I'm not going out
with Niecy anymore.

17:16.790 --> 17:18.880
Well, I appreciate that.

17:18.880 --> 17:21.670
And I'm sorry I upset you.

17:21.670 --> 17:23.670
You know, it was kind of
reckless of me

17:23.670 --> 17:25.670
to hook up with someone
from your church.

17:25.670 --> 17:29.500
The truth is, is that wasn't
what bothered me.

17:29.500 --> 17:31.750
You know Grandma
don't really give a damn

17:31.750 --> 17:32.960
about what people think.

17:32.960 --> 17:34.330
Then what made you so angry?

17:34.330 --> 17:36.540
Oh, I don't know.

17:36.540 --> 17:39.120
You were supposed to be
off at college

17:39.120 --> 17:41.580
getting your swerve on.

17:41.580 --> 17:44.040
But now you're doing
this gap year thing,

17:44.040 --> 17:47.880
and it's all happening
in front of me.

17:47.880 --> 17:51.750
You becoming a man
caught me off guard.

17:52.830 --> 17:54.000
I get that.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.330
It's gonna take me a minute
to get used to

17:56.330 --> 17:59.790
seeing my little grandbaby
as a man.

18:02.080 --> 18:03.460
I'll work on that.

18:05.120 --> 18:07.830
So, do men still hug
their grandmas?

18:09.880 --> 18:10.830
Come here.

18:10.830 --> 18:13.620
[ Laughs ]
Come here.

18:13.620 --> 18:15.250
[ Chuckles ] Aww.

18:15.250 --> 18:17.250
♪♪

18:17.250 --> 18:18.830
Diane:
I can't believe this.

18:18.830 --> 18:20.210
Jack:
Do we have to go in?

18:20.210 --> 18:21.670
Yeah, can't we just
call in sick?

18:21.670 --> 18:23.790
Or do that cruise ship school
like Zack and Cody?

18:23.790 --> 18:28.120
Look, guys, we know today
is not gonna be easy.

18:28.120 --> 18:30.960
And we are so sorry
for interfering.

18:30.960 --> 18:32.880
But there are
just some things

18:32.880 --> 18:36.710
that you are gonna need
to handle on your own now.

18:36.710 --> 18:37.500
Okay?

18:37.500 --> 18:39.460
No, not okay.
Wha--

18:39.460 --> 18:40.750
You did this.

18:40.750 --> 18:43.120
I'm gonna have to eat lunch
in the bathroom because of you.

18:43.120 --> 18:44.830
Yeah, you two walk us
into this school.

18:44.830 --> 18:46.000
Be our human shield.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.040
We -- We can't.

18:47.040 --> 18:49.290
We're gonna have to
be hands-off.

18:49.290 --> 18:52.580
All right? It's -- It's --
It's what's best.

18:52.580 --> 18:56.330
Well, isn't that convenient
for you, Andre.

18:56.330 --> 18:57.880
Let's just
get this over with.

19:00.000 --> 19:01.620
Have a --
Have a wonderful day.

19:01.620 --> 19:03.250
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

19:06.920 --> 19:08.960
It's like watching
"The Green Mile."

19:08.960 --> 19:11.290
Yeah.
Dead twins walking.

19:11.290 --> 19:13.830
Okay, Dre, I know I said
that we wouldn't help,

19:13.830 --> 19:15.170
but I --

19:15.170 --> 19:16.960
I have an idea.
Okay.

19:16.960 --> 19:18.380
What if we do help them?

19:18.380 --> 19:19.460
We can't, all right,

19:19.460 --> 19:21.250
even though I want to,
all right?

19:21.250 --> 19:23.080
But they have to do this.

19:23.080 --> 19:24.580
You're right.

19:24.580 --> 19:26.580
[ Sighs ]

19:26.580 --> 19:28.120
Let's get out of here.
[ Dinging ]

19:29.380 --> 19:30.830
Use your camera.

19:30.830 --> 19:32.670
I got it right here.

19:32.670 --> 19:34.170
Oh, there's the twins.

19:34.170 --> 19:36.040
Oh, God.
Th-They can't do it.

19:36.920 --> 19:39.750
You're wrong.
Our kids can't do it.

19:39.750 --> 19:42.000
[ Gasps ]
They've been exiled.

19:42.000 --> 19:43.880
Damn you, seventh grade.

19:43.880 --> 19:45.670
You are not going to believe
what happened.

19:45.670 --> 19:48.000
The haunted house was so scary
Cameron peed himself.

19:48.000 --> 19:48.920
Yeah.

19:48.920 --> 19:50.290
Cameron Carter
peed himself?

19:50.290 --> 19:52.380
A kid that pees himself
doesn't get full name status.

19:52.380 --> 19:54.540
And now everyone's calling him
Pee Pee Carter.

19:54.540 --> 19:56.880
And now we're cool because
it happened at our house.

19:56.880 --> 19:58.380
Oh! Oh, okay.

19:58.380 --> 19:59.710
We're back on top!

19:59.710 --> 20:01.540
Middle school is going to
be amazing from here on out.

20:01.540 --> 20:02.750
Nothing's gonna
bring us down.

20:02.750 --> 20:03.710
[ School bell rings ]
-Okay.
-Oh, okay.

20:03.710 --> 20:04.830
Bye.
I told you.

20:04.830 --> 20:06.290
Okay.
Bigger, blacker, deffer!

20:06.290 --> 20:07.460
Okay, okay, babe.

20:07.460 --> 20:09.080
[ Chuckles ]

20:09.080 --> 20:10.170
I give 'em about
two days, though,

20:10.170 --> 20:11.380
and they're gonna be
brought down.

20:11.380 --> 20:14.540
Well, let's let them
live this moment.

20:14.540 --> 20:15.620
Okay.

20:16.960 --> 20:18.330
Bye, Pee Pee Carter!

20:18.330 --> 20:20.040
Dre, get -- Roll up
the window! I'm going.

20:23.960 --> 20:25.330
So my kids were growing up

20:25.330 --> 20:27.000
and learning how to handle
their own business.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.330
And I realized
it was time to handle

20:29.330 --> 20:32.710
some unfinished business
of my own.

20:32.710 --> 20:35.120
Because if you're true
to yourself,

20:35.120 --> 20:37.580
it doesn't matter
what people say.

20:39.210 --> 20:41.750
Hey, everybody.
Dre's got a purse!

20:41.750 --> 20:44.290
That's right [bleep]

20:44.290 --> 20:45.880
You think
I could pull that off?

20:45.880 --> 20:47.710
Shorts? No.

20:47.710 --> 20:49.540
But that purse, though?

20:49.540 --> 20:50.710
Also no.
